William Henry Millard (25 May 1856 – 20 July 1923) was an English cricketer.  Millard was a right-handed batting whose bowling style is unknown.  He was born at New Swindon, Wiltshire.
Millard made his first-class debut for Sussex against Kent at the County Ground, Hove.  He made four further first-class appearances for the county, the last of which came against the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1880.  In his five first-class matches, he scored a total of 54 runs at an average of 6.75, with a high score of 26.  With the ball, he took 2 wickets at a bowling average of 22.00, with best figures of 2/32.He died at Tenby, Pembrokeshire, Wales on 20 July 1923.
